originalText.text: I bought a monthly spot here for October and November through SpotHero. All the of attendants were nice except for one who repeatedly complained to me about dog hair in my car. I vacuumed my car before returning it to the garage each time, and he continued to complain about covering his body in alcohol after getting out of my car to prevent an allergic reaction. I’m not a doctor, but I’ve never heard of covering your body in alcohol to combat pet allergies. I’ll never return to this garage and wouldn’t recommend it to anyone because I was afraid my car would be damaged by this person. Plenty of other garages in the neighborhood!

originalText.text:
I bought a monthly parking pass through Spot Hero for June and then for July and August I paid directly to the garage (at their request to save them fees from Spot Hero). Most of the guys on staff were nice but there were a few that were incredibly rude.  One employee told me that I didn't give enough notice and I'd have to wait (I gave over 2 hours notice). He laughed in my face and mumbled things under his breath when all I did was ask how much longer.  It was clear to me that the hour text prior to arriving was not enough for them and even when I texted 4-5 hours ahead my car still wasn't there when I arrived.  When I dropped my car off they hounded me about when I would be back and sometimes I wasn't sure of the date and they would give me dirty looks or just walk away. I always tried to give as much notice as possible but I can't control every single time.

At first the manager was very nice but over the last month I noticed his attitude changed.  He was not as polite and would cut me off mid sentence.

I have an older car which is clearly not as nice as many of the vehicles in the garage and I think that they treated me a little less because of it.  I watched them politely wish others a good morning or good evening but I barely got a hello.

I would not recommend this garage based off of the employees and their poor attitudes towards me.  I'm sure if they're treating me this way I can't be the only one.

originalText.text: I am a monthly parker at the facility.  The whole team is great and very responsive.  I have never had an issue getting the car on a timely basis (noting that I always provide at least an hour's notice).  I really like that the garage is ground level and big - no ramps, etc.
